sudo yum update -y
sudo yum install -y git curl
Install Node.js and npm:
Step 2: Install Node.js and npm
curl -fsSL https://rpm.nodesource.com/setup_16.x | sudo bash -
sudo yum install -y nodejs 
Verify the installation:
node -v
npm -v
Step 3: Clone Your Angular Frontend Repository 
git clone <your-repository-url>
cd angular-frontend
Step 4: Install Angular CLI and Build the App 
Install Angular CLI globally:
⦁	sudo npm install -g @angular/cli
Install project dependencies:
⦁	npm install
Build the application for production:
⦁	ng build --prod
Step 5: Serve the Application 
Install a static server (e.g., http-server):
⦁	sudo npm install -g http-server
Serve the built application:
⦁	cd dist/<project-name> # Replace <project-name> with your Angular project name
⦁	http-server -p 80
